\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Cost--safety tradeoff across the six stopping policies on the ambiguity stress replay (L4, 18 streams). \textsc  {Fixed Burst} is cheapest but fails entirely under first-window ambiguity (re-escalation rate 1.0). \textsc  {Stability Stop}, \textsc  {Marginal Utility Stop}, and \textsc  {Repeated Fixed Burst} occupy a middle tier (re-escalation rate 0.83). \textsc  {Counter-Recovery Stop} and \textsc  {Hybrid Stop} eliminate re-escalation entirely at modest additional tracing cost. Markers within a tied cluster are spread horizontally for legibility; exact values are reported in Table~\ref {tab:rq4-stress}.}}{8}{}\protected@file@percent }
